commitResults.messageBody:
Duke contains too many methods. Some of the methods are just for
interacting with the user; some are just loading and saving tasks to
file; some are just dealing with user inputs; some are involved with
manipulating the list of tasks; the rest is just printing out responses
made by the chatbot.

This causes the code to be hard to follow along.

Extracting the methods into their respective classes delegates
responsibilities to the classes and makes it easier to refactor certain
behaviour of Duke by just refactoring only the class that handles this
behaviour.

commitResults.messageBody:
There are many related classes belonging to the root duke package.

These related classes cause duke package to be congested and hard to
follow along.

Let's group DukeException and FileParseException into an exception
package within the duke package. Similarly, let's group Storage and
TaskStorage into a storage package. Finally, let's group Cli, Gui
and Ui into a ui package.

This makes it easier to find exception-related code, storage-related
code and ui-related code respectively.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions
commitResults.messageBody:
Assertions help to define assumptions about the program state so that
the runtime can verify them. These definitions are useful to programmers
working on the repo in future.

Let's verify that
- the file we are reading the user's data from exists after a storage is
constructed to store the file content.
- the file content stored in the storage is up-to-date with changes made
to the file.
- for tasks that consists of a date, these tasks have a date after being
constructed.

commitResults.messageTitle: Rename all variables of type TaskList
commitResults.messageBody:
For variables of type TaskList, tasks is mainly used.

Let's rename all these variables named tasks to taskList.

tasks is mainly used to refer to ArrayList<Task>, and
TaskList behaves similarly to ArrayList<Task>. Renaming tasks
to taskList for variables of type TaskList helps reduce
confusion between the two.

commitResults.messageBody:
Ui is handling user input by parsing it.

It is not the job of ui to do so.

Let's delegate this function to Parser instead, and take advantage of
